    "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nThis is a draft for the formal specifications of the `OP_CHECKCONTRACTVERIFY` (`CCV`) opcode.\r\n\r\n`CCV` enables to build Script-based state machines that span across multiple transactions, by providing an ergonomic tool to commit to - and introspect - the Script and possibly some _data_ that is committed inside inputs or outputs.\r\n\r\nRelated to this PR:\r\n- Implementation in bitcoin-core PR (TODO: add link).\r\n- [Post on delving bitcoin](https://delvingbitcoin.org/t/op-checkcontractverify-and-its-amount-semantic/1527), focusing on the amount logic of the opcode.\r\n\r\nNot covered in this draft:\r\n- sigops budget (benchmarks needed)\r\n- activation logic\r\n- policy considerations (if any)\r\n\r\nI recommend delving bitcoin for high level discussions about alternative implementations, applications, etc.",
